The first of three memorial services for Joseph Shabalala was held in his home town of Ladysmith. JOHANNESBURG - A memorial service for late Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala was held in his home town of Ladysmith. It was the first of three memorial services. Shabalala died at a Pretoria hospital on Tuesday after a long illness at the age of 78. READ: Ramaphosa declares special official funeral for Joseph Shabalala His deteriorating health forced him to retire from the group in 2014. A second memorial service will be held in Durban on Wednesday, while a third will be held in Johannesburg on Thursday. The special official funeral will be held on Saturday at the AG Magubane Stadium in Ladysmith.